A police officer was shot dead on Friday night by gunmen he was pursuing in Kayole, Nairobi. Boniface Okech of Soweto police station was shot as he and his colleagues sought a gang said to be on a robbery spree.Nairobi police boss Japheth Koome said the suspects were spotted, prompting a chase that turned fatal.In another incident in Pangani, three suspected criminals were killed in a botched robbery.They were said to be mugging residents who alerted police.Friday night continued on a bloody note as two other suspects were gunned down in Utawala area in a botched robbery.On the same day, a video surfaced allegedly of police killing two suspected gang members in Eastleigh.The minute-long clip shows a person thought to be a police in plain clothes apprehending a suspect. The body of another suspect covered in blood lies in the middle of the road.[VIDEO] Cops caught on camera killing suspected Eastleigh gang members, Boinnet orders probeAnother man in police uniform holding what looks like an AK-47 rifle is seen dispersing the crowd.When the suspect tries to struggle with the alleged plain clothes officer, he is shot at close range.The clip has drawn condemnation on social media and IG Joseph Boinnet has called for a probe on the incident.IPOA has also said it is looking into the incident.